I am not entirely sure myself yet. Actually my friend is working on a good website: www.permacultured.net  about ecology. He's much better at this stuff than me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/img/em/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  or ecology.com. I think the Kyote thing was more sybolic than anything, but it is a step, however shaky.<br>
<br>
&quot;Why not have huge incentives for people to purchase hybrid cars or conversions and raise gas taxes to pay for those incentives?&quot;<br>
<br>
That is the type of thing we need to be doing. We all need to be using our cars a little less. I think it has to be a slow change, but a complete change. <br>
